  "prompt": "What is the latency on Google Maps traffic updates?",
  "response": "Google Maps generally updates traffic information in real-time, utilizing data from a variety of sources such as GPS data from mobile devices, government and private traffic sensors, and user feedback. The latency or delay in these updates can vary but is typically quite minimal, often within a few minutes. Factors such as the volume of data, server processing times, and the efficiency of data integration can influence the exact latency. However, for most users, the traffic updates provided by Google Maps are considered to be highly current and useful for real-time navigation and planning.",
